9Lives is a rapidly expanding veterinary group with multiple veterinary offices, ranging from GP to ER. We started as a feline only practice and have expanded to provide 24/7 ER.  All hospitals are fully equipped with digital radiography, ultrasound, in house blood machines, etc. We have a brand-new CT scan in our 24-hour facility, and we will be offering ambulance service to help our patients transfer between locations as needed. Our nursing staff is fully bilingual and can assist with all of your translation needs.  We are committed to providing continuing education and learning opportunities abound.

 Job Highlights

Experience in handling animals;
Shift duty is required;
Fringe benefits, medical insurance, commission scheme, 13-month salary

 Veterinary Nurses

 Job Description

Support animal handling during consultations, examinations, testing, X-ray and surgeries, as assigned;
Dispense medication as instructed by veterinary doctors and explain dosage and precautions to customers;
Look after hospitalized animals, which include cleaning, feeding and etc;
Act as translators between clients and veterinary staff (English and Cantonese) during consultation;
Manage customers services, such as registrations, billing and etc.
Support inventory control, record of movements and ordering; Perform regular stocktake and check expiry dates; 
Perform any other duties, as assigned.

 Requirements

Excellent spoken English and Cantonese and good interpersonal skills;
Passionate in animal welfare;
Candidates with AIRC Certificate at Grade 2 / Grade 4 is an advantage;
Shift duty is required, including Saturday, Sunday and public holidays
Immediate available is preferred;

 Offer

- Our salary package commensurate with experience and qualifications;

- Fringe benefits included medical Insurance, commission scheme, overtime compensation, 13-month salary and staff discount.

